.TH "ssam_controller_start" 9 "ssam_controller_start" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ssam_controller_start \- Start the receiver and transmitter threads of the controller.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ssam_controller_start
.BI "(struct ssam_controller *ctrl "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctrl" 12
The controller.
.SH "NOTE"
When this function is called, the controller should be properly
hooked up to the serdev core via \fIstruct serdev_device_ops\fP. Please refer
to \fBssam_controller_init\fP for more details on controller initialization.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function must be called with the main controller lock held (i.e. by
calling \fBssam_controller_lock\fP).
